  "notes": [
    "This is a Generic EPD covering the Gold Coast region (Queensland, Australia). Plants included: Labrador, Stapylton, and Burleigh.",
    "The EPD document covers many other concrete mix products in addition to the primary declared product HyLo-50 Normal-Class 25 MPa (EPD-IES-0014958:001). Other products in the same document include: 25 MPa with 4.6 kg/m3 Blended Polyfibre, 32 MPa with 4.6 kg/m3 Blended Polyfibre, Burnish 40 MPa, Blockfill 20/25/32/40 MPa, High Workability 40-100 MPa, HyColour 25/32/40 MPa, HyGrade 20/25/32/40/50 MPa, HyLite 25/32 MPa, HyShine 32/40 MPa, HySpray 25/32/40 MPa, HyLo-40 Normal-Class 20/25/32/40/50MPa, HyLo-50 Normal-Class 20/32/40/50 MPa, Kerb, Lean Mix, Piling, Post-tensioned, Stabilised Sand, TMR variants, and others.",
    "B1 value (-3.28 kg CO2 eq.) represents recarbonation during service life (carbonation uptake) as modeled in the GCCA tool.",
    "GWP-fos value for A1-A3 reads 1.41E+02 which is the same as GWP-tot; the biogenic and luluc components are very small (0.027 and 0.0217 respectively), so GWP-fossil ≈ GWP-total.",
    "Compressive strength listed as '25' in the product table without explicit test age; 28-day assumed as standard.",
    "Full lifecycle GWP-tot (A1-A3 through D) is approximately 167 kg CO2 eq./m3 as shown in the product comparison table on page 22."
  ]
